name: neleqtrrd
params: class c0, class c1, class c2, wff w0

body.origin:
|- wi(w0, wn(wcel(c0, c1)))
-| wi(w0, wn(wcel(c0, c2)))
-| wi(w0, wceq(c2, c1))

cumulated.origin:
|- wi(w0, wn(wcel(c0, c1)))
-| wi(w0, wn(wcel(c0, c2)))
-| wi(w0, wceq(c2, c1))

body.origin:
|- wi(w0, wceq(c2, c1))
-| wi(w0, wceq(c1, c2))

cumulated.origin:
|- wi(w0, wn(wcel(c0, c1)))
-| wi(w0, wn(wcel(c0, c2)))

comment: If a class is not an element of another class, it is also not an element of an equal class. Deduction form. (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.) (Proof shortened by Wolf Lammen, 13-Nov-2019.)
